= AIST5030 Mini-Project Report

== Introduction

In the mini-project, we finetuned a Small Language Model (SLM) to complete Fill-in-the-Middle (FIM) tasks resource-efficiently specifically for Rust, a modern, memory-safe programming language, using the parameter-efficient Orthogonal Finetuning (OFT) method. The source code of this mini-project is located at #link("https://github.com/hack3ric/oft-slm-rust").

== Methodology

=== Fill-in-the-Middle Tasks

Fill-in-the-Middle (FIM) is an advanced code completion task where a model learns to generate missing code by analyzing both the preceding and succeeding context, mimicking modern IDE autocomplete tools. A basic prompt structure used for FIM is shown in @fim-prompt, which includes the current open file's name alongside the code located immediately before and after the cursor, as visualized in @code-editor.

