=== Model, Dataset, and Configuration

This project utilized the _Qwen2.5-1.5B-Instruct_ model, a highly capable SLM, finetuned on the _Etherll/CodeFIM-Rust-Mellum_ dataset. This dataset contains approximately 57,000 FIM examples specifically designed for training intelligent Rust code completion.

We applied OFT targeting the model's attention and MLP layers with a rank of 8. The training was conducted using a learning rate of $2^(-4)$ over 2 epochs, culminating in 2,500 total steps to ensure steady convergence without overfitting.

== Experiment

=== Hardware and Data Setup

Training was executed on a single NVIDIA RTX 6000 Ada GPU. The dataset was partitioned into 40,000 items for the training phase and 6,920 items for quantitative evaluation.

=== Training

Training took approximately 4.5 hours and yielded a highly stable loss curve (@loss-curve), dropping from 1.2 to 0.5. The sharp decrease near step 1250 reflects a learning rate adjustment or epoch boundary, allowing the optimizer to quickly settle into a deeper minimum. Ultimately, the loss converged smoothly, confirming the OFT adapter successfully learned the FIM patterns without instability.

